      <table>
         <tgroup cols="3">
            <colspec colname="COLSPEC1"/>
            <colspec colname="col2"/>
            <colspec colname="col3"/>
            <thead>
               <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                     <p>Issue</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry valign="top">
                     <p>Check</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry valign="top">
                     <p>Action</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>No LEDs are active on the LUFP7 gateway.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>
                        <sl>
                           <sli>Check the health status of the DC supply </sli>
                           <sli>Check the polarity of the gateway DC supply</sli>
                        </sl>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>If the DC voltage supply is OK and the polarity is correct
and no LED is active, the device needs to be checked by a maintenance
engineer.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry morerows="1">
                     <p>No communication
on the Profibus bus.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>That the RJ45 cable from the Ethernet patch panel is connected to
the right port on the gateway.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Change the cable to the Modbus port on the gateway.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Incorrect gateway address.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Set the gateway address to the correct default value according to
the table in chapter <xref href="Default_Address_for_the_Gateways_CPT_0000414788.xml"
                              scope="local"
                              type="concept"/>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry morerows="4">
                     <p>No signal
on the Modbus network, the LED (5) is red.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Check the addresses for the secondary devices on the Modbus RTU network.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Set the device Modbus address to the correct default value according
to the tables in chapter <xref href="Modbus_RTU_Device_Address_CPT_0000419180.xml"
                              scope="local"
                              type="concept"/>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Check that the wiring between the secondary Modbus devices and the
Ethernet patch panel.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="1">Correct wiring according to the electrical
drawings and the specifications in the chapter <xref href="Modbus_Wiring_for_Modbus-Porfibus_DP_Converter_CPT_0000405596.xml"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"/>.</entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Check the Modbus wiring between components (IM400, IFL12MC).</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Check if any of the secondary Modbus devices (IM400, IFL12MC) are
inoperative. If the Reality status LED is red on any device.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>If the Reality status LED is red, the device needs to be checked
by a maintenance engineer.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Check that the gateway is using the correct config file depending
on solution type (PEW/SDC). For PEW solutions also check that the
config file has the correct setup order (A060/A062/A064).</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Replace the config file with the correct config file.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry morerows="1">
                     <p>No communication
with the config port of the LUFP7 gateway.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Check that the straight PowerSuite cable (VW3 A8 106) is connected
to the config port and not the Modbus port.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Connect the straight PowerSuite cable (VW3 A8 106) to the config
port of the gateway.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Check the correct COM port number.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <p>Set the correct COM port number.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
            </tbody>
         </tgroup>
      </table>
